#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:5.1"
msgid "11. Kosiyasikkhāpada"
msgstr "11. The training rule on silk"

#. </h1></div><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Origin story"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="1"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.224"></a><a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.71"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.11.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2098"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.2"
msgid "Tena samayena buddho bhagavā āḷaviyaṃ viharati aggāḷave cetiye."
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying at Āḷavī at the Aggāḷava Shrine."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.3"
msgid "Tena kho pana samayena chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kosiyakārake upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadanti—"
msgstr "At that time monks from the group of six approached some silk-makers and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.4"
msgid "“bahū, āvuso, kosakārake pacatha, amhākampi dassatha,"
msgstr "“Boil many silkworms and give us silk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.5"
msgid "mayampi icchāma kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kātun”ti."
msgstr "We wish to make blankets containing silk.”"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.6"
msgid "Te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "The silk-makers grumbled and complained,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.7"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma samaṇā sakyaputtiyā amhe upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhanti—"
msgstr "“How can the Sakyan ascetics approach us and say "

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.8"
msgid "‘bahū, āvuso, kosakārake pacatha, amhākampi dassatha, mayampi icchāma kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kātun’ti."
msgstr "such a thing?"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:6.9"
msgid "Amhākampi alābhā, amhākampi dulladdhaṃ, ye mayaṃ ājīvassa hetu puttadārassa kāraṇā bahū khuddake pāṇe saṅghātaṃ āpādemā”ti."
msgstr "It’s our misfortune that we must cause the death of many small creatures because of our livelihood and because of our wives and children.”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2099"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:7.1"
msgid "Assosuṃ kho bhikkhū tesaṃ manussānaṃ ujjhāyantānaṃ khiyyantānaṃ vipācentānaṃ."
msgstr "Monks heard the complaints of those silk-makers,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:7.2"
msgid "Ye te bhikkhū appicchā … pe …"
msgstr "and the monks of few desires …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:7.3"
msgid "te ujjhāyanti khiyyanti vipācenti—"
msgstr "complained and criticized those monks,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:7.4"
msgid "“kathañhi nāma chabbaggiyā bhikkhū kosiyakārake upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhanti—"
msgstr "“How can those monks from the group of six approach silk-makers and say"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:7.5"
msgid "‘bahū, āvuso, kosakārake pacatha, amhākampi dassatha, mayampi icchāma kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kātun’”ti."
msgstr "such a thing?”"

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="3"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2100"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.1"
msgid "Atha kho te bhikkhū chabbaggiye bhikkhū anekapariyāyena vigarahitvā bhagavato etamatthaṃ ārocesuṃ … pe …"
msgstr "After criticizing them in many ways, they informed the Master. …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.2"
msgid "“saccaṃ kira tumhe, bhikkhave, kosiyakārake upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vadetha—"
msgstr "“Is it true, monks, that you approached silk-makers and said,"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.3"
msgid "‘bahū, āvuso, kosakārake pacatha, amhākampi dassatha,"
msgstr "‘Boil many silkworms and give us silk."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.4"
msgid "mayampi icchāma kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kātun’”ti?"
msgstr "We wish to make blankets containing silk’?”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.5"
msgid "“Saccaṃ, bhagavā”ti."
msgstr "“It’s true, Master.”"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.6"
msgid "Vigarahi buddho bhagavā … pe …"
msgstr "The Buddha rebuked them:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.7"
msgid "kathañhi nāma tumhe, moghapurisā, kosiyakārake upasaṅkamitvā evaṃ vakkhatha—"
msgstr "“Foolish men, how can you approach silk-makers and say"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.8"
msgid "‘bahū, āvuso, kosakārake pacatha, amhākampi dassatha, mayampi icchāma kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kātun’ti."
msgstr "such a thing?"

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.72"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.9"
msgid "Netaṃ, moghapurisā, appasannānaṃ vā pasādāya … pe …"
msgstr "This will not give rise to confidence in those without it …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:8.10"
msgid "evañca pana, bhikkhave, imaṃ sikkhāpadaṃ uddiseyyātha—"
msgstr "And, monks, this training rule should be recited thus:"

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:9.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Final ruling"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="4"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2101"></a>
#. <strong class="rule"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:9.2"
msgid "“Yo pana bhikkhu kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kārāpeyya, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyan”ti."
msgstr "‘If a monk gets a blanket made that contains silk, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession.’”"

#. </strong> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:9.3"
msgid "(<em>11</em>:<strong>30</strong>)"
msgstr ""

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Definitions"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="5"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.11.2"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.11.2.1"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2102"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.2"
msgid "Yo panāti"
msgstr "A:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.3"
msgctxt "yo yādiso … pe …"
msgstr "whoever …"

#. </span><strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.4"
msgid "bhikkhūti"
msgstr "Monk:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.5"
msgctxt "… pe …"
msgstr "… The monk who has been given the full ordination by a complete Order through a formal procedure consisting of one motion and three announcements that is unchallengeable and fit to stand—"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:10.6"
msgid "ayaṃ imasmiṃ atthe adhippeto bhikkhūti."
msgstr "this sort of monk is meant in this case."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="6"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2103"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:11.1"
msgid "Santhataṃ nāma"
msgstr "A blanket:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:11.2"
msgctxt "santharitvā kataṃ hoti avāyimaṃ."
msgstr "it is made by spreading out, not by weaving."

#. </span></p><p><a class="sc" id="7"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2104"></a>
#. <strong class="term"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.1"
msgid "Kārāpeyyāti"
msgstr "Gets made:"

#. </strong><span class="gloss"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.2"
msgctxt "ekenapi kosiyaṃsunā missitvā karoti vā kārāpeti vā, payoge dukkaṭaṃ."
msgstr "in the effort of making a blanket that contains even one thread of silk, or in getting one made, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.3"
msgid "Paṭilābhena nissaggiyaṃ hoti."
msgstr "When he gets the blanket, it becomes subject to relinquishment."

#. </span></p><hr><p>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.4"
msgid "Nissajjitabbaṃ saṃghassa vā gaṇassa vā puggalassa vā."
msgstr "The blanket should be relinquished to an Order, a group, or an individual."

#. <span class="kamma"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.5"
msgid "Evañca pana, bhikkhave, nissajjitabbaṃ …"
msgstr "“And, monks, it should be relinquished in this way. …"

#. <span class="add"> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.6"
msgid "pe …"
msgstr "To be expanded as in <a href=\"/en/pi-tv-bu-vb-np1#13\">Relinquishment 1, paragraphs 13–17</a>, with appropriate substitutions. …"

#. </span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.7"
msgid "idaṃ me, bhante, kosiyamissakaṃ santhataṃ kārāpitaṃ nissaggiyaṃ."
msgstr "‘Venerables, this blanket containing silk which I got made is to be relinquished."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.8"
msgid "Imāhaṃ saṃghassa nissajjāmīti … pe …"
msgstr "I relinquish it to the Order.’ …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.9"
msgid "dadeyyāti … pe …"
msgstr "the Order should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.10"
msgid "dadeyyunti … pe …"
msgstr "you should give …"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:12.11"
msgid "āyasmato dammīti."
msgstr "‘I give this blanket back to you.’”"

#. </span></p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:13.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Permutations"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="8"></a><a class="pts-vp-pi" id="pts-vp-pi3.225"></a><a class="pts-cs" id="bu-np.11.2.2"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2105"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:13.2"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:13.3"
msgid "Attanā vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what he began himself, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:13.4"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ attanā pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he finishes himself what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:13.5"
msgid "Parehi vippakataṃ parehi pariyosāpeti, nissaggiyaṃ pācittiyaṃ."
msgstr "If he gets others to finish what was begun by others, he commits an offense entailing relinquishment and confession."

#. </p><p><a class="sc" id="9"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2106"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:14.1"
msgid "Aññassatthāya karoti vā kārāpeti vā, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he makes one, or gets one made, for someone else, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. <a class="pts-vp-en" id="bd.2.73"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:14.2"
msgid "Aññena kataṃ paṭilabhitvā paribhuñjati, āpatti dukkaṭassa."
msgstr "If he obtains one that was made by someone else and then uses it, he commits an offense of wrong conduct."

#. </p><h2>
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:15.1"
msgid ""
msgstr "Non-offenses"

#. </h2><p><a class="sc" id="10"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2107"></a> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:15.2"
msgid "Anāpatti—"
msgstr "There is no offense:"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:15.3"
msgid "vitānaṃ vā bhūmattharaṇaṃ vā sāṇipākāraṃ vā bhisiṃ vā bibbohanaṃ vā karoti,"
msgstr "if he makes a canopy, a floor cover, a screen-wall, a mattress, or a pillow;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:15.4"
msgid "ummattakassa,"
msgstr "if he is insane;"

msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:15.5"
msgid "ādikammikassāti."
msgstr "if he is the first offender."

#. </p><hr><p class="endsutta"><a class="sc" id="11"></a><a class="wt-pa" id="2108"></a>
#. <span class="note" hidden>It is called the first rule in the Pali since it is the first rule of the second chapter on relinquishment. If, however, one disregards the division into chapters, it is the eleventh rule on relinquishment.</span> 
msgctxt "pi-tv-bu-vb-np11:16.1"
msgid "Kosiyasikkhāpadaṃ niṭṭhitaṃ paṭhamaṃ."
msgstr "The first rule, the training rule on silk, is finished."

